hopobject.body: Whereabouts are you from? viagra kaufen auf rechnung In this photo released by the Syrian official news agency SANA, a Syrian man stands in rubble at the scene of a car bomb attack in Qamishli, 497 miles (800 Kilometers) northeast Damascus, Syria, Sunday, Sept. 30, 2012. A suicide attacker detonates a car bomb at a Syrian security compound in a remote, predominantly Kurdish area, killing at least four people in the latest sign that Syria's largest ethnic minority is increasingly being drawn into a widening civil war.
